==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[odour]]'', from Old French ''odour'', from Latin ''odor''.

===Alternative spellings===
* [[odour]]

===Noun===
'''odor''' (''plural:'' ''[[odors]]'')

# Any [[smell]], whether fragrant or offensive; [[scent]]; [[perfume]].
# A strong, pervasive [[quality]].
# [[Esteem]]; [[repute]].

